  <para>
    When the <varname>condition</varname> parameter of a <xref
    linkend="RegisteredClass-ConditionalIteration"/> is set to
    <classname>ReductionRate</classname>, iteration of a <xref
    linkend="RegisteredClass-SkeletonModifier"/> will stop when the
    rate of decrease of the <link
    linkend="Section-Concepts-Skeleton-Energy">effective energy</link>
    of the &skel; falls below the given
    <varname>reduction_rate</varname> threshold.
  </para>
  <para>
    The energy reduction rate is defined as
    <equation>
      <alt role="tex">
	\[
	\mathrm{Reduction\ Rate} = 
	\frac{E_\mathrm{before} - E_\mathrm{after}}{E_\mathrm{before}}
	\times 100
	\]
      </alt>
    </equation>
    where
    <inlineequation>
      <alt role="tex">\(E_\mathrm{before}\)</alt>
    </inlineequation>
    and
    <inlineequation>
      <alt role="tex">\(E_\mathrm{after}\)</alt>
    </inlineequation>
    are the total &skel; energies before
    and after the last iteration of the <xref
    linkend="RegisteredClass-SkeletonModifier"/>.
  </para>

